original_font_information.description: Science Gothic is a variable font, designed by Thomas Phinney, Vassil Kateliev and Brandon Buerkle, with a little help from Igor Freiberger early on. The basic design is based on Morris Fuller Benton’s Bank Gothic (1930–34), for American Type Founders. Science Gothic builds on and extends Benton’s design by adding a lowercase, much more extreme variation in weight and width, and a stroke contrast axis. The latter allows for part of the range that is somewhat reminiscent of other period designs such as Benton’s Broadway (1927), and R. Hunter Middleton’s Radiant (circa 1938–40) for Ludlow.
